# =============================================================================
# Devloop .gitignore Template
# =============================================================================
# Copy this content to your project's .gitignore file to properly manage
# which .claude/ files are tracked vs local-only.
#
# Usage:
#   cat plugins/devloop/templates/gitignore-devloop >> .gitignore
#
# Or manually copy the sections you need.
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Claude Code Local Settings (DO NOT COMMIT)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Personal Claude Code configuration - different per machine/user
.claude/settings.local.json

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Devloop Local Configuration (DO NOT COMMIT)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Personal preferences like enforcement level, model preferences
# Each developer may have different settings
.claude/devloop.local.md

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Security Audit Outputs (DO NOT COMMIT)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Security reports may contain sensitive vulnerability details
# Should be addressed and closed, not preserved in git history
# Especially important for public repositories
.claude/security/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Spike Investigation Reports (DO NOT COMMIT)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Exploratory working notes from /devloop:spike
# Conclusions flow into the plan; reports are transient
# May contain rejected approaches or dead ends
.claude/*-spike-report.md

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional: Session Summaries (Depends on Workflow)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Uncomment if you want to keep session summaries local
# Some teams prefer to commit these for context preservation
# .claude/session-summary.md

# =============================================================================
# Files That SHOULD Be Tracked (for reference - don't add these to .gitignore)
# =============================================================================
# These files are intentionally NOT ignored and should be committed:
#
# .claude/devloop-plan.md       - Active implementation plan (shared state)
# .claude/devloop-worklog.md    - Completed work history (team reference)
# .claude/project-context.json  - Tech stack cache (speeds up session start)
# .claude/issues/                - Issue tracking (bugs, features, tasks)
# .claude/commands/              - Project-specific slash commands
#
# If any of these are being ignored, check for conflicting .gitignore patterns

# =============================================================================
# Troubleshooting
# =============================================================================
# If files are still being tracked after adding this:
#
# 1. Check if they were already committed:
#    git ls-files .claude/
#
# 2. Remove from tracking (but keep local file):
#    git rm --cached .claude/devloop.local.md
#    git rm --cached .claude/settings.local.json
#    git rm --cached -r .claude/security/
#
# 3. Commit the .gitignore changes:
#    git add .gitignore && git commit -m "chore: add devloop gitignore patterns"
#
# See also: Skill: file-locations for complete documentation
